      "start": 18.58,
      "end": 20.84,
      "text": "Green KRI.com",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 23.16,
      "end": 24.1,
      "text": "Asap's Fables",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 26.2,
      "end": 27.96,
      "text": "The Horse and the Groom",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 29.66,
      "end": 34.86,
      "text": "There was once a groom who used to spend long hours clipping and combing the horse of",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 34.86,
      "end": 39.8,
      "text": "which he had charge, but who daily stole a portion of his allowance of oats and sold",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 39.8,
      "end": 40.72,
      "text": "it for his own profit.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 41.76,
      "end": 46.82,
      "text": "The horse gradually got into worse and worse condition, and at last cried to the groom,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 46.82,
      "end": 52.26,
      "text": "If you really want me to look sleek and well, you must comb me less and feed me more.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 55.5,
      "end": 57.78,
      "text": "End of the Horse and the Groom",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
